cs.HC, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper investigates code comprehension from a physiological and cognitive perspective, using lightweight biometric sensors to classify the type of comprehension tasks performed by developers. This suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the use of machine learning models to automatically identify tasks suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.NE). Finally, the study's use of physiological signals to understand cognitive processes may also suggest a focus on cybernetics (cs.CY).
